entry.title: Add an absolute threshold to heuristic memory saver
entry.content:
This finch-controllable threshold must be exceeded as well as the %

threshold for discarding to start happening. This is to avoid cases

the threshold is set to e.g. 5%, and we want to avoid discarding on a

machine with 128Gb of installed RAM that has 6Gb free.



In this case, the absolute threshold could be set to e.g. 1Gb, which

would result in an 8Gb machine starting to discard tabs at 5% remaining

but the 128Gb machine would start discarding when it has 1Gb available.

entry.title: [BSC]: Fix failing BSC `GoogleURLLoader` unittests
entry.content:
`net::cookie_util::IsDomainMatch` relies that the domain has a '.'

prefix. Therefore, it return false for `accounts.google.com` and

`google.com`. This CL uses `GURL::DomainIs` to ensure bound session

requests are correctly blocked when the cookie is expired.



`BoundSessionParams::domain` reflects a domain that is configured by

Gaia as part of the registration flow for a bound session. It instructs

the browser on which request requires the short lived cookie regardless

of the actual domain of the cookie. At this point

`BoundSessionParams::domain` is set based on

`GaiaUrls::GetInstance()->secure_google_url()` as the registration flow

is not implemented yet and does not contain a '.' prefix.

entry.title: Fix Autofill address callback in Settings.
entry.content:
The bug is reproducible after opening an Incognito window.

PDM::Init() call in the Incognito mode is called with the same instances

of `AutofillWebDataService` (`profile_database`, `account_database`) as

the origin profile (this is how `chrome::GetBrowserContextRedirectedInIncognito(context)`

works, see `WebDataServiceFactory::GetAutofillWebDataForProfile` and

`WebDataServiceFactory::GetBrowserContextToUse`) overriding the

`on_autofill_profile_changed_cb_` callback in

`AutofillWebDataBackendImpl`.



Hence the symptoms: added addresses are not lost, Sync knows about

updates, but updates do not appear on the page until `PDM::Refresh()`

is called somewhere (e.g. by adding a Credit card).

entry.title: dlp: Make warning modal to the Files app
entry.content:
Modifies DLP Files warning dialog to be modal to the Files app, if one

is opened. If no windows can be found, the dialog is created as a

system modal. This will be changed to open a new Files app instance in

later CLs.



Currently, the Files app window is detected in the DlpFilesController,

when processing requests for file open/share, drag n drop, transfer.

When we support the new notifications which allow the user to "Review",

we can pass the exact Files app window in which the notification was

handled and use this as the modal parent.



When no opened Files app windows can be found (e.g. when "Review"-ing

from a system notification), we will still retrieve the last active

Files app window, or create a new one.

entry.title: [Code Health] Migrate BackgroundFetchRegistration to GC mojo wrappers.
entry.content:
BackgroundFetchRegistration's registration_service_ becomes a

HeapMojoRemote, and thus is initialized with an execution context.



This means that when the registration service is bound with the

registration interface, it needs a task runner. Since this task runner

is moved in this process, it needs to be a different task runner than

the one already used in the ctor.



Because the execution context provides the task runner, in the case of

a nullptr or destroyed execution context, the registration service

will not be bound; this is a change from the prior implementation.



Fixed: 1426369

entry.content:
When a user connects to a network using a EAP authentication method that

requires a server CA certificate and selects the default certificate as

a server CA certificate, the validation rules enforce setting a

domainSuffixMatch or subjectAltNameMatch.



This CL relaxes the validation rules for managed networks because the

values of domainSuffixMatch and subjectAltNameMatch are not controlled

by the user in this case.

entry.title: Mojo API for opening URLs without interception by URL capturing.
entry.content:
The gotcha is that the JavaScript `window.open(url)` has a page

transition of `ui::PAGE_TRANSITION_LINK`, which can be intercepted by

URL capturing.

- Specifying a different page transition prevents interception logic.

- I chose `ui::PAGE_TRANSITION_FROM_API` [1] which suits our use case,

i.e. transition originating from an external application.



Note that this function only accepts https:// URLs and will always open

the specified URL in a new browser tab.

- Failure to provide a valid https:// URL will cause the Help app

renderer process to crash.



[1]: https://source.chromium.org/chromium/chromium/src/+/main:ui/base/page_transition_types.h;l=137;drc=3e1a26c44c024d97dc9a4c09bbc6a2365398ca2c

This patch changes the `item_index_` and `offset_` pair to

`NGInlineItemTextIndex` to keep related two indexes together

and for better readability.

* `NGInlineBreakToken`: Remove the `item_index` and `offset`

constructor, preferring specific type over `unsigned`.

* `NGInlineItemResult`: Add `Start()` and `End()` that return

`NGInlineItemTextIndex`.

* `NGInlineItemTextIndex`: Add `operator==` and `ostream`

support to use it in `DCHECK_EQ`.

* `NGBoxFragmentBuilder`: Use `NGInlineItemTextIndex` to

construct `NGInlineBreakToken`.



This patch has no behavior changes.
